
Yolo Hiker is a website developed by Tuleyome (an advocacyoriented nonprofit organization focused on protecting both the wild and agricultural heritages of the PutahCache bioregion).  It contains descriptions of trails and hiking and backpacking hikes with Yolo County as the point of origin, dates for group outings such as the Capay Valley Hiking Club hikes, whitewater rafting outings, GPS files, maps, images of the region, etc.  There is an email mailing list that you can join to receive announcements of upcoming hikes and issues related to hiking and outdoor activities outdoor recreation.


